  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>General</Type>
    <Text>This is a well-located first-class hotel for the leisure or business travellers.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>SurroundingArea</Type>
    <Text>The hotel is situated in Siam Square. It is a 10 minute walk to Central World Plaza and a 5 minute walk to Mah Boon Krong (MBK) Centre. The hotel is in a prime area with access to a sky train interchange station.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>RoomTypes</Type>
    <Text>The rooms are medium-sized and offer nice views of the city. All the rooms are simply decorated in pastel colours, with carpeted floors but no balconies. The rooms come equipped with a full range of modern amenities. WiFi Internet access is available in room free of charge. The bathrooms are in good condition and are finished in black marble.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>PropertyInformation</Type>
    <Text>This hotel is an 18-storey modern white high-rise building. The front of the building is set back from the road in four tiered steps.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>DiningFacilities</Type>
    <Text>The Chinese restaurant serves Cantonese and Szechuan cuisine, whilst the cafe features Thai, continental, Japanese and Chinese cuisine. There is a popular entertainment complex in the hotel's basement, where parties are held with live bands and karaoke. The lounge offers the perfect rendezvous to meet friends or to simply relax with a drink and features live classical chamber music performances and nightly piano bar entertainment.</Text>
  </Description>
  <Description>
    <Language>en</Language>
    <Type>Short</Type>
    <Text>The lobby is large, with an attractive marble floor, extensive seating area and adjacent lobby lounge. In the evenings, the live music in the lounge makes the lobby a very pleasant place in which to relax.</Text>
  </Description>
